{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_48","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc \"nl -ba docs/pipeline_notes.md | sed -n '30,90p'\"","aggregated_output":"    30\tThe active preset also refreshes the path named by `config.paths.selected_root_ids`\n    31\tso downstream pipeline steps can switch subsets without code changes.\n    32\t\n    33\t### Geometry handoff contract\n    34\t\n    35\tMilestone 5 uses the versioned geometry bundle contract\n    36\t`geometry_bundle.v1`. One canonical library path builder owns the\n    37\tfilenames below, and both `scripts/02_fetch_meshes.py` plus\n    38\t`scripts/03_build_wave_assets.py` use it directly.\n    39\t\n    40\tPer neuron, the bundle layout is:\n    41\t\n    42\t- `config.paths.meshes_raw_dir/<root_id>.ply`: raw mesh\n    43\t- `config.paths.skeletons_raw_dir/<root_id>.swc`: raw skeleton\n    44\t- `config.paths.processed_mesh_dir/<root_id>.ply`: simplified mesh\n    45\t- `config.paths.processed_graph_dir/<root_id>_graph.npz`: surface graph\n    46\t- `config.paths.processed_graph_dir/<root_id>_patch_graph.npz`: patch graph\n    47\t- `config.paths.processed_graph_dir/<root_id>_descriptors.json`: derived descriptor sidecar\n    48\t- `config.paths.processed_graph_dir/<root_id>_qa.json`: QA sidecar\n    49\t\n    50\tThe processed graph archives intentionally separate fine and coarse data:\n    51\t\n    52\t- the surface graph stores the simplified mesh vertices/faces, sparse surface adjacency/Laplacian arrays, and `surface_to_patch` so every surface vertex has an explicit coarse patch assignment\n    53\t- the patch graph stores sparse coarse adjacency/Laplacian arrays plus `patch_sizes`, `patch_centroids`, `patch_seed_vertices`, and CSR-style `member_vertex_indices` / `member_vertex_indptr` arrays for reconstructing patch membership deterministically\n    54\t\n    55\t`config.paths.manifest_json` records the bundle contract version, dataset,\n    56\tmaterialization version, meshing-config snapshot, and per-root asset\n    57\tstatuses/paths. Raw fetch runs also record `raw_asset_provenance` per\n    58\troot ID so cache hits, refetches, skips, validation failures, and\n    59\toptional skeleton fetch errors can be audited without reading console\n    60\tlogs. Processed bundle records also expose `artifact_sources` so each\n    61\tsimplified mesh, surface graph, patch graph, and sidecar points back to\n    62\tthe raw mesh and skeleton inputs it was built against.\n    63\t\n    64\tCompatibility shim:\n    65\t\n    66\t- `config.paths.processed_graph_dir/<root_id>_meta.json` is still written as\n    67\t  a legacy metadata pointer so older consumers can keep reading the prior\n    68\t  sidecar name during migration.\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
